2)What are the Enviroments ? Types?

Answer:
--------
A code environment is a standalone and self-contained environment to run Python. Each code environment has its own set of packages.
Environments are independent:
--------------------------------
you can install different packages or different ersions of packages in different environments without interaction between them.
Types are as follows:
-------------------------
* Text-Editors.
* IDEs.
* Notebook Environments.
